\page demo6 Qate - demo 6 - Kate based syntax highligher

\b Next \ref demo7

This example shows how to use the Qate synatx highlighter instead of QtSourceView.
The implementation of QtSourceView has some issues (can be very slow for medium sized
documents), and you cannot nest definitions.

Qate, not only works in O(1), (where n is the number of rules defined in the language,
) also each iteration of QtSourceView iterarion uses internaly regular expressions, which
are very slow.

A small snipet of code for using this library:


\code
#include "qate/context.h"
#include "qate/highlighter.h"
#include "qate/highlightdefinition.h"
#include "qate/highlightdefinitionmanager.h"
#include "qate/defaultcolors.h"

Qate::Theme theme;
Qate::MimeDatabase *mimes;
Qate::HighlightDefinitionManager *hl_manager;
TextEditor::Internal::Highlighter *highlighter;
QSharedPointer<TextEditor::Internal::HighlightDefinition> highlight_definition;
QPlainTextEdit *textEditor;

textEditor = new QPlainTextEdit(main_window);
highlighter = new TextEditor::Internal::Highlighter(text_editor->document());
theme.setupDefaultColors();
theme.applyToHighlighter(highlighter);
theme.applyToEditor(textEditor);

highlight_definition = hl_manager->definition( hl_manager->definitionIdByName("Perl") );
if (!highlight_definition.isNull())
        highlighter->setDefaultContext(highlight_definition->initialContext());
\endcode

